1
00:00:03,440 --> 00:00:04,480
Nong.

2
00:00:06,080 --> 00:00:07,760
I have something to confess to you.

3
00:00:10,040 --> 00:00:11,160
Yes?

4
00:00:13,600 --> 00:00:15,400
Well…

5
00:00:19,720 --> 00:00:21,240
I got a woman pregnant.

6
00:00:29,640 --> 00:00:30,640
Mr. Rut?

7
00:00:34,320 --> 00:00:36,520
What did you just say?

8
00:00:38,760 --> 00:00:41,000
So…

9
00:00:42,080 --> 00:00:43,800
How am I supposed to feel?

10
00:00:45,320 --> 00:00:47,120
- Do we have to break up?
- Oh.

11
00:00:47,200 --> 00:00:49,120
No, no, Anong.

12
00:00:49,200 --> 00:00:51,680
No, I'm not breaking up with you.

13
00:00:52,440 --> 00:00:53,720
I won't.

14
00:00:54,440 --> 00:00:55,680
Then…

15
00:00:56,680 --> 00:00:58,920
what should I do?

16
00:01:00,680 --> 00:01:02,760
What exactly happened?

17
00:01:06,760 --> 00:01:07,840
I made a mistake.

18
00:01:11,080 --> 00:01:13,840
Is something like that even a mistake?

19
00:01:16,720 --> 00:01:19,000
That day, I was drunk.

20
00:01:19,080 --> 00:01:20,960
Very drunk. I lost control.

21
00:01:21,040 --> 00:01:23,360
And when I lost control, it just happened.

22
00:01:24,400 --> 00:01:27,280
But Anong, I don't love her.

23
00:01:28,560 --> 00:01:29,880
I love you.

24
00:01:32,840 --> 00:01:34,400
Then what are you going to do…

25
00:01:36,400 --> 00:01:38,440
about the child?

26
00:01:42,200 --> 00:01:43,280
Uh…

27
00:01:46,480 --> 00:01:48,640
At first, I thought

28
00:01:49,160 --> 00:01:50,120
I'd raise it myself.

29
00:01:51,560 --> 00:01:52,560
Or…

30
00:01:52,640 --> 00:01:54,840
find someone else to take responsibility.

31
00:01:55,760 --> 00:01:57,760
How could that be possible?

32
00:02:02,400 --> 00:02:03,600
It is…

33
00:02:05,880 --> 00:02:08,400
if that woman is Praewilai.

34
00:02:09,479 --> 00:02:10,680
Sarut.

35
00:04:52,520 --> 00:04:54,280
Sin, Anong,

36
00:04:54,920 --> 00:04:57,640
please let my son go. Please.

37
00:04:58,560 --> 00:04:59,960
At least we once lived together.

38
00:05:00,040 --> 00:05:01,560
- Let him go?
- Ugh.

39
00:05:02,120 --> 00:05:03,520
What do you mean let go?

40
00:05:05,120 --> 00:05:06,400
Have you forgotten?

41
00:05:08,400 --> 00:05:10,560
The reason Warat ended up like this

42
00:05:11,080 --> 00:05:12,360
is because of you.

43
00:05:16,840 --> 00:05:18,520
Don't tell me

44
00:05:19,120 --> 00:05:20,480
you don't remember.

45
00:05:31,600 --> 00:05:33,040
I got a woman pregnant.

46
00:05:38,480 --> 00:05:39,760
Do we have to break up?

47
00:05:39,840 --> 00:05:43,400
No, no, Anong. No,

48
00:05:43,480 --> 00:05:44,760
I'm not breaking up with you.

49
00:05:45,880 --> 00:05:47,440
Then what are you going to do…

50
00:05:49,320 --> 00:05:51,240
about the child?

51
00:05:54,280 --> 00:05:55,400
What just happened

52
00:05:55,920 --> 00:05:59,960
was probably a father
showing love to his son

53
00:06:00,040 --> 00:06:01,440
for the first

54
00:06:02,920 --> 00:06:04,560
and the last time.

55
00:06:07,320 --> 00:06:08,400
"Warat, my son."

56
00:06:11,120 --> 00:06:14,480
Do you know how disgusted I am by you?!

57
00:06:15,400 --> 00:06:16,680
Aren't you the one

58
00:06:16,760 --> 00:06:19,720
who abandoned him
before he was even born?!

59
00:06:21,440 --> 00:06:22,440
Huh.

60
00:06:25,360 --> 00:06:27,120
Mr. Warat, don't be afraid.

61
00:06:27,800 --> 00:06:32,360
Because I've already
taken revenge for you.

62
00:06:34,760 --> 00:06:35,680
Anong.

63
00:06:36,760 --> 00:06:38,680
What do you mean by that?

64
00:06:40,360 --> 00:06:41,400
Huh?

65
00:06:42,560 --> 00:06:44,280
It means

66
00:06:44,360 --> 00:06:47,520
every dose of medicine you've been taking

67
00:06:48,360 --> 00:06:50,760
has made you unable to walk.

68
00:07:01,960 --> 00:07:03,600
Anong, hey!

69
00:07:08,160 --> 00:07:10,040
If you could still walk normally,

70
00:07:10,560 --> 00:07:12,200
my plan with Sin

71
00:07:12,720 --> 00:07:14,920
wouldn't have succeeded this easily.

72
00:07:15,000 --> 00:07:17,160
Anong! Anong!

73
00:07:17,680 --> 00:07:18,960
Ugh!

74
00:07:25,240 --> 00:07:26,640
We should be close now.

75
00:07:27,880 --> 00:07:30,160
But when we get there,
Kluay and Som, don't get out of the car.

76
00:07:30,240 --> 00:07:31,200
Why not?

77
00:07:31,280 --> 00:07:32,520
It's dangerous.

78
00:07:32,600 --> 00:07:33,800
Then I can go down.

79
00:07:33,880 --> 00:07:34,840
No.

80
00:07:34,920 --> 00:07:36,440
Why not? I want to help.

81
00:07:36,520 --> 00:07:38,080
I told you, it's dangerous.

82
00:07:38,160 --> 00:07:40,640
It's exactly because it's dangerous
that we should go help together.

83
00:07:40,720 --> 00:07:42,640
We don't even know if they have a gun.

84
00:07:42,720 --> 00:07:46,640
That's exactly why, Arnon. How can
you go alone? We should go together.

85
00:07:46,720 --> 00:07:47,560
I'm worried about you.

86
00:07:47,640 --> 00:07:49,040
I'm worried about you too.

87
00:07:49,120 --> 00:07:50,520
Why won't you listen?

88
00:07:50,600 --> 00:07:52,480
- You're the one not listening.
- Uh.

89
00:07:52,560 --> 00:07:54,480
Calm down, both of you.

90
00:07:54,560 --> 00:07:57,000
Mr. Arnon, who do you think is there?

91
00:07:58,280 --> 00:07:59,520
Probably Jirasin.

92
00:08:00,560 --> 00:08:02,240
Anyone else?

93
00:08:03,200 --> 00:08:04,160
I don't think so.

94
00:08:04,680 --> 00:08:07,960
Even Chatchai didn't know
what Jirasin was doing.

95
00:08:09,560 --> 00:08:11,880
Then I think
we should all go down together.

96
00:08:11,960 --> 00:08:12,800
But…

97
00:08:12,880 --> 00:08:15,440
Arnon, we can help each other.

98
00:08:15,520 --> 00:08:17,400
- Well…
- Arnon,

99
00:08:17,480 --> 00:08:20,880
don't just worry about us.
We worry about you too.

100
00:08:20,960 --> 00:08:22,920
We'll go help Mr. Warat together.

101
00:08:23,000 --> 00:08:24,800
- Well--
- Everyone has to be safe.

102
00:08:24,880 --> 00:08:26,200
- Som, listen.
- Arnon,

103
00:08:26,880 --> 00:08:29,440
if something happens to you

104
00:08:29,520 --> 00:08:31,160
or to Mr. Warat,

105
00:08:31,880 --> 00:08:33,400
how are Kluay and I supposed to go on?

106
00:08:33,480 --> 00:08:34,559
She's right.

107
00:08:36,960 --> 00:08:39,840
Alright.
But promise me one thing, both of you.

108
00:08:39,919 --> 00:08:41,760
If anything happens,

109
00:08:42,280 --> 00:08:45,840
run away immediately.

110
00:08:58,040 --> 00:08:58,880
Son.

111
00:09:00,680 --> 00:09:03,760
I'm sorry. I really am.

112
00:09:04,560 --> 00:09:06,200
Don't call me your son.

113
00:09:09,040 --> 00:09:10,280
Someone like you…

114
00:09:12,680 --> 00:09:13,760
doesn't deserve to be anyone's father.

115
00:09:17,440 --> 00:09:19,680
The only father I have is Mr. Wichan.

116
00:09:21,520 --> 00:09:22,760
Wichan?

117
00:09:48,280 --> 00:09:52,000
MR. WICHAN VANICH

118
00:10:21,160 --> 00:10:23,320
It's me, Nong. No need to get up.

119
00:10:23,840 --> 00:10:26,840
I just came to thank you.

120
00:10:27,600 --> 00:10:28,680
Thank me for what?

121
00:10:29,520 --> 00:10:31,760
I'm thanking you

122
00:10:32,520 --> 00:10:36,600
for raising Mr. Sarut's son so well.

123
00:10:37,560 --> 00:10:39,600
- You…
- Oh, not quite.

124
00:10:39,680 --> 00:10:41,800
I should say

125
00:10:41,880 --> 00:10:43,240
thank you

126
00:10:43,320 --> 00:10:47,840
for handing over all of the Vanich fortune
to Mr. Warat.

127
00:10:53,360 --> 00:10:54,600
What did you do?

128
00:10:54,680 --> 00:10:56,480
Don't get up.

129
00:10:57,440 --> 00:10:58,800
By now,

130
00:10:59,440 --> 00:11:02,880
the poison has already
entered your bloodstream.

131
00:11:04,200 --> 00:11:05,600
Help… help!

132
00:11:12,720 --> 00:11:13,960
Everyone

133
00:11:14,480 --> 00:11:16,920
has to die eventually.

134
00:11:17,000 --> 00:11:19,040
Don't be afraid.

135
00:11:19,120 --> 00:11:20,760
You won't be alone.

136
00:11:20,840 --> 00:11:23,240
Because when you die,

137
00:11:23,320 --> 00:11:27,680
I'll send Mr. Warat to keep you company.

138
00:11:50,840 --> 00:11:52,600
Rest well.

139
00:11:57,280 --> 00:11:58,360
Dad…

140
00:12:00,840 --> 00:12:02,560
That's Mr. Warat's car.

141
00:12:02,640 --> 00:12:04,160
He's here.

142
00:12:05,200 --> 00:12:07,160
Should we wait for the police?

143
00:12:07,240 --> 00:12:08,920
Mr. Supol probably already called them.

144
00:12:09,000 --> 00:12:10,240
We can't wait.

145
00:12:10,840 --> 00:12:13,520
If Mr. Warat is really here,
we have to go in now.

146
00:12:17,360 --> 00:12:18,920
You fake son,

147
00:12:20,120 --> 00:12:22,440
why are you so emotional?

148
00:12:23,760 --> 00:12:26,120
He's not even your real father.

149
00:12:26,840 --> 00:12:27,800
Ms. Anong.

150
00:12:29,560 --> 00:12:30,480
Sin.

151
00:12:33,160 --> 00:12:34,080
Ugh!

152
00:12:35,640 --> 00:12:36,880
They have a gun.

153
00:12:37,400 --> 00:12:39,000
- Mr. Warat.
- Ms. Kluay, don't.

154
00:12:39,520 --> 00:12:41,680
I think before we go in,
we need a plan first.

155
00:12:43,760 --> 00:12:46,000
Sin! You…

156
00:12:46,720 --> 00:12:47,960
Sin,

157
00:12:48,040 --> 00:12:49,560
what do you want?

158
00:12:50,080 --> 00:12:52,520
Why? You think
you can get it all back for me?

159
00:12:52,600 --> 00:12:53,640
Yes.

160
00:12:55,080 --> 00:12:56,520
If I get it all back for you,

161
00:12:57,480 --> 00:12:58,760
will we be even?

162
00:12:58,840 --> 00:13:02,160
If it weren't for you and your mom
everyone would still be with me.

163
00:13:04,920 --> 00:13:10,640
<i>Little yellow oriole</i>

164
00:13:11,720 --> 00:13:16,760
<i>Where will you sleep tonight…</i>

165
00:13:17,920 --> 00:13:19,840
Mom, you're so good.

166
00:13:20,760 --> 00:13:24,560
When you were little,
she used to sing you this lullaby too.

167
00:13:24,640 --> 00:13:26,080
Really?

168
00:13:26,160 --> 00:13:30,000
Yes, Sin.
You used to fall asleep so easily.

169
00:13:30,080 --> 00:13:33,320
So you have to love Mom the most, okay?

170
00:13:33,400 --> 00:13:34,800
- I love you, Mom.
- Mm.

171
00:13:34,880 --> 00:13:37,080
You have to love your father a lot too.

172
00:13:37,160 --> 00:13:38,960
- I love you, Dad.
- Mm.

173
00:13:39,040 --> 00:13:41,240
I love everyone.

174
00:13:41,320 --> 00:13:43,400
- Really?
- Yes.

175
00:13:47,440 --> 00:13:50,200
I want my family back.
I want my parents back.

176
00:13:50,280 --> 00:13:52,320
I want my sister back!
Can you give them back to me?!

177
00:13:53,000 --> 00:13:54,480
What are you talking about?

178
00:13:54,560 --> 00:13:56,160
If not for you…

179
00:13:56,680 --> 00:13:59,760
Hey, Sin, don't!

180
00:14:01,120 --> 00:14:02,360
Sin!

181
00:14:08,000 --> 00:14:08,840
Ms. Ampha?

182
00:14:27,000 --> 00:14:28,280
- Uh.
- But… Oh?

183
00:14:28,360 --> 00:14:29,600
- Ms. Kluay.
- Kluay.

184
00:14:33,600 --> 00:14:35,520
Ah! Don't!

185
00:14:40,240 --> 00:14:42,160
Be careful, son.

186
00:14:42,960 --> 00:14:43,880
Mr. Warat.

187
00:14:45,920 --> 00:14:47,400
Kluay, why are you here?

188
00:14:51,600 --> 00:14:54,000
- You!
- Hey! Don't!

189
00:14:54,840 --> 00:14:55,800
- Ms. Anong.
- Aunt Nong.

190
00:14:55,880 --> 00:14:56,840
Aunt Nong.

191
00:14:57,640 --> 00:14:58,640
Kluay!

192
00:14:58,720 --> 00:14:59,720
Ms. Anong, please stop.

193
00:14:59,800 --> 00:15:01,280
- Ms. Kluay, be careful.
- Ms. Anong.

194
00:15:01,360 --> 00:15:03,160
- Anong!
- Ms. Anong.

195
00:15:04,280 --> 00:15:05,360
- Ms. Anong, please stop.
- Don't.

196
00:15:06,040 --> 00:15:07,720
- Ugh!
- Aunt Nong.

197
00:15:12,480 --> 00:15:13,640
Mom.

198
00:15:21,760 --> 00:15:22,600
Hey.

199
00:15:24,600 --> 00:15:26,160
Chatchai.

200
00:15:26,240 --> 00:15:28,520
Jirasin, turn yourself in.

201
00:15:28,600 --> 00:15:29,720
You should be the one doing that.

202
00:15:29,800 --> 00:15:32,560
Chatchai, tell Jirasin why you're here.

203
00:15:33,280 --> 00:15:36,680
If you can stop him
from fighting Mr. Warat,

204
00:15:36,760 --> 00:15:40,360
I'll ask Mrs. Wanee
to bring you back to work.

205
00:15:41,080 --> 00:15:41,920
Mr. Sin,

206
00:15:43,040 --> 00:15:43,800
I'm here to help.

207
00:15:43,880 --> 00:15:45,320
Mr. Warat, watch out!

208
00:15:45,400 --> 00:15:47,320
Get down!

209
00:15:47,920 --> 00:15:50,120
Chatchai, calm down.

210
00:15:50,200 --> 00:15:51,800
All of you will die today.

211
00:15:51,880 --> 00:15:53,280
No!

212
00:15:54,000 --> 00:15:54,960
- Sin!
- Don't.

213
00:15:58,400 --> 00:15:59,320
Hey.

214
00:16:03,880 --> 00:16:05,000
Hey.

215
00:16:06,880 --> 00:16:08,080
Don't!

216
00:16:08,160 --> 00:16:09,160
Now.

217
00:16:39,800 --> 00:16:40,800
That voice…

218
00:16:44,520 --> 00:16:45,640
Mom.

219
00:16:59,240 --> 00:17:00,360
Mom!

220
00:17:03,680 --> 00:17:04,560
Mr. Arnon.

221
00:17:12,079 --> 00:17:13,640
Mr. CEO,

222
00:17:13,720 --> 00:17:15,520
if I spare your life,

223
00:17:15,599 --> 00:17:18,560
- what will you give me?
- Shoot him, Chatchai.

224
00:17:20,079 --> 00:17:21,160
Calm down, Mr. Sin.

225
00:17:22,040 --> 00:17:23,000
Drop the gun.

226
00:17:23,079 --> 00:17:25,200
- Chatchai, what are you doing?
- Now.

227
00:17:30,320 --> 00:17:33,280
Now the power is in my hands, not yours.

228
00:17:36,520 --> 00:17:37,360
Are you ready to transfer?

229
00:17:38,120 --> 00:17:39,680
If he dies, all the shares will be mine.

230
00:17:40,480 --> 00:17:41,520
What are you talking about?

231
00:17:41,600 --> 00:17:43,440
I want Vanich's shares.

232
00:17:43,520 --> 00:17:44,760
I'll give you half.

233
00:17:44,840 --> 00:17:45,960
That's enough.

234
00:17:46,480 --> 00:17:48,200
Don't let this escalate any further.

235
00:17:48,840 --> 00:17:49,760
Don't.

236
00:17:51,560 --> 00:17:52,960
Fine, Chatchai.

237
00:17:54,840 --> 00:17:56,240
I'll give you everything.

238
00:17:56,960 --> 00:17:59,280
Now that sounds better, Mr. CEO.

239
00:18:00,320 --> 00:18:01,440
What do you want?

240
00:18:01,520 --> 00:18:03,400
Money? Gold? Shares?

241
00:18:04,120 --> 00:18:05,360
I'll give you everything.

242
00:18:05,440 --> 00:18:07,960
I was going to take it all anyway.

243
00:18:08,720 --> 00:18:09,560
Mr. Sin,

244
00:18:12,440 --> 00:18:14,440
I'll deal with all four of them.

245
00:18:15,280 --> 00:18:16,600
But you take the blame for me.

246
00:18:17,200 --> 00:18:19,120
Fine. I'll give you everything.

247
00:18:19,200 --> 00:18:21,560
As long as they're dead, I'm satisfied.

248
00:18:33,400 --> 00:18:35,040
<i>All of you should die.</i>

249
00:18:35,120 --> 00:18:37,040
<i>All of you should die.</i>

250
00:18:37,600 --> 00:18:39,440
<i>- All of you should die.</i>
- What is this?

251
00:18:40,080 --> 00:18:41,680
<i>All of you should die.</i>

252
00:18:43,440 --> 00:18:45,640
- Ugh.
<i>- All of you should die.</i>

253
00:18:46,160 --> 00:18:49,480
<i>- All of you should die.</i>
- Mr. Sin, I…

254
00:18:50,000 --> 00:18:51,960
- No, Chatchai.
<i>- All of you should die.</i>

255
00:18:52,040 --> 00:18:57,400
<i>All of you should die.</i>
<i>All of you should die.</i>

256
00:18:58,000 --> 00:18:58,880
<i>All of you should die.</i>

257
00:18:58,960 --> 00:19:01,000
I can't control myself…

258
00:19:03,720 --> 00:19:06,800
<i>- All of you should die.</i>
- No, don't.

259
00:19:06,880 --> 00:19:08,440
Aunt Nong, help me.

260
00:19:15,760 --> 00:19:17,240
Aunt Nong, he's back.

261
00:19:17,320 --> 00:19:19,320
Warat, the one you said killed my mother.

262
00:19:19,400 --> 00:19:21,080
Warat's back?

263
00:19:21,160 --> 00:19:24,320
Yes. He finished his studies
and took the executive position.

264
00:19:24,840 --> 00:19:26,240
- I want to kill him myself.
- Oh.

265
00:19:27,640 --> 00:19:29,440
Don't worry. He'll die soon enough.

266
00:19:30,200 --> 00:19:31,600
What do you mean?

267
00:19:32,800 --> 00:19:36,120
Evil people get what they deserve.

268
00:19:36,640 --> 00:19:38,280
Don't you think so, Sin?

269
00:19:38,800 --> 00:19:40,840
Sin!

270
00:19:43,680 --> 00:19:44,680
Sin!

271
00:19:45,680 --> 00:19:47,080
Sin! Sin!

272
00:19:47,160 --> 00:19:49,080
- Aunt Nong…
- Sin!

273
00:19:49,920 --> 00:19:50,960
Sin!

274
00:19:51,920 --> 00:19:53,280
Aunt Nong…

275
00:19:53,360 --> 00:19:54,680
Help me…

276
00:20:05,040 --> 00:20:06,960
Mr. Sin. Mr. Sin.

277
00:20:07,480 --> 00:20:10,680
Mr. Sin. I didn't do it.

278
00:20:12,920 --> 00:20:13,960
Sin.

279
00:20:16,480 --> 00:20:17,360
Aunt Nong.

280
00:20:17,440 --> 00:20:20,760
Sin, don't speak. Don't say anything.

281
00:20:20,840 --> 00:20:21,880
I…

282
00:20:22,880 --> 00:20:25,440
I'll get to see my family again.

283
00:20:27,200 --> 00:20:29,880
No, Sin! You're not going anywhere.

284
00:20:29,960 --> 00:20:32,200
You have to stay with me!
You have to stay.

285
00:20:32,280 --> 00:20:34,360
Don't go anywhere.

286
00:20:42,760 --> 00:20:45,640
Sin, have you been home long?

287
00:20:50,560 --> 00:20:53,160
I wanted to ask you something.

288
00:20:53,240 --> 00:20:56,240
I designed this building today, right?

289
00:20:56,320 --> 00:20:58,360
But the engineers

290
00:20:58,440 --> 00:21:00,800
said it can't be built.

291
00:21:01,320 --> 00:21:03,640
Can you take a look
and see if it can be built or not?

292
00:21:22,280 --> 00:21:23,880
Why are you crying?

293
00:21:30,560 --> 00:21:32,080
Mom, Dad.

294
00:21:47,480 --> 00:21:50,360
I don't want to be alone anymore.

295
00:21:53,280 --> 00:21:55,640
Sin, it's just a nightmare.

296
00:21:56,760 --> 00:21:58,040
It's okay.

297
00:21:58,120 --> 00:21:59,960
Don't cry, Sin.

298
00:22:00,040 --> 00:22:02,680
I don't want to have nightmares anymore.

299
00:22:04,440 --> 00:22:05,800
Mom.

300
00:22:05,880 --> 00:22:08,160
Oh, Sin.

301
00:22:12,120 --> 00:22:13,800
Don't cry.

302
00:22:15,320 --> 00:22:16,880
It's okay.

303
00:22:18,920 --> 00:22:21,360
Dad, Mom.

304
00:22:23,080 --> 00:22:24,080
<i>No, Sin!</i>

305
00:22:24,160 --> 00:22:27,000
You have to stay with me!

306
00:22:35,400 --> 00:22:37,640
Sin.

307
00:22:43,680 --> 00:22:47,920
Sin, wake up. Stay with me.

308
00:22:51,160 --> 00:22:52,720
Sin.

309
00:22:53,360 --> 00:22:55,600
Don't leave me.

310
00:22:56,200 --> 00:22:57,920
Sin, no.

311
00:23:00,600 --> 00:23:02,760
Don't leave me.

312
00:23:12,840 --> 00:23:14,680
<i>All of you should die.</i>

313
00:23:15,320 --> 00:23:16,160
<i>All of you should die.</i>

314
00:23:17,800 --> 00:23:19,360
<i>All of you should die.</i>

315
00:23:19,880 --> 00:23:22,560
<i>All of you should die.</i>

316
00:23:22,640 --> 00:23:24,440
<i>All of you should die.</i>

317
00:23:24,520 --> 00:23:26,760
<i>- All of you should die.</i>
<i>- Die. Die!</i>

318
00:23:27,840 --> 00:23:28,680
Ms. Anong.

319
00:23:30,640 --> 00:23:32,080
Anong, don't!

320
00:23:33,120 --> 00:23:34,680
- Anong.
- Ms. Anong.

321
00:23:35,280 --> 00:23:36,800
<i>All of you should die.</i>

322
00:23:38,560 --> 00:23:40,640
<i>All of you should die.</i>

323
00:23:58,960 --> 00:24:00,200
Anong.

324
00:24:01,920 --> 00:24:03,040
Anong.

325
00:24:04,080 --> 00:24:05,800
Please let me go, Anong.

326
00:24:10,400 --> 00:24:12,520
What did I ever do to you?

327
00:24:14,520 --> 00:24:16,120
Please, let me go.

328
00:24:18,120 --> 00:24:19,680
If you won't do it for me,

329
00:24:21,480 --> 00:24:23,200
then do it for the children.

330
00:24:25,240 --> 00:24:26,840
I have Waree

331
00:24:27,960 --> 00:24:30,720
and Warat to take care of.

332
00:24:36,280 --> 00:24:38,040
If you don't let me go,

333
00:24:39,600 --> 00:24:42,280
I will come after you.

334
00:24:43,480 --> 00:24:45,800
I will destroy your life.

335
00:24:48,920 --> 00:24:50,560
But if you come to your senses,

336
00:24:53,920 --> 00:24:55,760
and let me go back to the children,

337
00:24:57,160 --> 00:24:59,120
let me raise them,

338
00:25:05,480 --> 00:25:07,880
I won't hold anything against you.

339
00:25:09,320 --> 00:25:11,640
I will forgive you for everything.

340
00:25:15,120 --> 00:25:16,240
Anong.

341
00:25:20,000 --> 00:25:22,440
Please let me go.

342
00:25:26,680 --> 00:25:27,840
Ampha.

343
00:25:28,920 --> 00:25:29,760
You…

344
00:25:35,280 --> 00:25:36,120
That's enough.

345
00:25:36,200 --> 00:25:37,400
<i>No.</i>

346
00:25:40,520 --> 00:25:41,400
That's enough.

347
00:25:41,480 --> 00:25:43,920
<i>She made an agreement. She has to die.</i>

348
00:25:47,720 --> 00:25:49,000
That's enough.

349
00:25:49,080 --> 00:25:50,240
<i>No.</i>

350
00:25:56,800 --> 00:25:58,160
I've forgiven her.

351
00:26:15,480 --> 00:26:17,080
Let's stop this together.

352
00:26:17,600 --> 00:26:18,760
<i>It's time for her to pay.</i>

353
00:26:19,920 --> 00:26:22,080
She has suffered enough.

354
00:26:22,160 --> 00:26:23,200
<i>No.</i>

355
00:26:26,600 --> 00:26:28,000
I know now that…

356
00:26:35,640 --> 00:26:36,720
Anong,

357
00:26:38,080 --> 00:26:39,600
I forgive you.

358
00:26:43,280 --> 00:26:45,240
<i>Nonsense. She has to die.</i>

359
00:26:48,240 --> 00:26:49,560
Let go of your hatred

360
00:26:51,680 --> 00:26:53,600
and live your life.

361
00:27:07,120 --> 00:27:08,200
Kluay.

362
00:27:19,120 --> 00:27:20,560
I love you, honey.

363
00:27:40,160 --> 00:27:41,720
- Mom, Mom.
- Kluay.

364
00:27:42,320 --> 00:27:44,840
Mom. Mom!

365
00:27:44,920 --> 00:27:47,600
Mom, come back to me.

366
00:27:48,280 --> 00:27:49,640
Mom!

367
00:27:51,240 --> 00:27:52,240
Mom…

368
00:27:54,720 --> 00:27:56,240
Mom.

369
00:27:59,200 --> 00:28:02,160
Please come back to me.

370
00:28:06,040 --> 00:28:07,520
Mom…

371
00:28:09,560 --> 00:28:12,080
Come back to me.

372
00:28:14,920 --> 00:28:16,280
Mom…

373
00:28:49,280 --> 00:28:50,320
Kluay.

374
00:28:55,280 --> 00:28:56,400
Where is Ms. Ampha?

375
00:28:59,360 --> 00:29:00,720
She's gone.

376
00:29:10,640 --> 00:29:11,560
Mr. Warat…

377
00:29:17,160 --> 00:29:18,080
What's wrong?

378
00:29:40,680 --> 00:29:41,880
Mom…

379
00:29:43,440 --> 00:29:45,320
Where did you go?

380
00:29:46,400 --> 00:29:49,400
Please come back to me.

381
00:29:55,720 --> 00:29:58,240
You must have suffered so much, right?

382
00:30:00,840 --> 00:30:02,480
I'm sorry.

383
00:30:06,760 --> 00:30:08,160
Let's go home.

384
00:30:12,200 --> 00:30:13,280
I, Waree,

385
00:30:14,320 --> 00:30:17,000
will take you home, Mom.

386
00:30:43,720 --> 00:30:48,760
BOONYAVEJ HOSPITAL

387
00:31:20,960 --> 00:31:22,040
Mr. Warat.

388
00:31:23,040 --> 00:31:25,200
Does it hurt anywhere?

389
00:31:27,760 --> 00:31:29,680
I'm still a bit sore.

390
00:31:29,760 --> 00:31:30,760
Mm.

391
00:31:31,480 --> 00:31:33,880
Of course you are,
after what you went through.

392
00:31:36,320 --> 00:31:37,160
Kluay,

393
00:31:40,440 --> 00:31:42,120
how long was I out?

394
00:31:42,640 --> 00:31:43,800
Mm.

395
00:31:44,400 --> 00:31:46,440
Quite a while.

396
00:31:46,520 --> 00:31:48,440
It's almost noon now.

397
00:31:51,760 --> 00:31:52,600
What about the others?

398
00:31:53,320 --> 00:31:54,560
How are they?

399
00:31:56,720 --> 00:31:58,400
Afterwards last night,

400
00:32:00,800 --> 00:32:01,640
<i>we got out</i>

401
00:32:01,720 --> 00:32:05,560
<i>and the police and forensic team</i>
<i>came to collect evidence.</i>

402
00:32:06,400 --> 00:32:08,640
<i>Ms. Anong was arrested at the scene.</i>

403
00:32:08,720 --> 00:32:11,960
<i>They had to separate her from Sin's body.</i>

404
00:32:13,040 --> 00:32:16,240
<i>They've already</i>
<i>taken Sin's body for autopsy.</i>

405
00:32:17,720 --> 00:32:19,280
<i>Sin,</i>

406
00:32:19,360 --> 00:32:21,720
<i>sometimes I understand you.</i>

407
00:32:22,240 --> 00:32:24,920
<i>But you shouldn't have done this.</i>

408
00:32:26,080 --> 00:32:28,840
<i>It wouldn't have changed anything.</i>

409
00:32:41,560 --> 00:32:43,240
<i>Chatchai turned himself in.</i>

410
00:32:43,320 --> 00:32:45,680
<i>But he's trying to fight the case.</i>

411
00:32:45,760 --> 00:32:49,200
<i>It's a criminal case,</i>
<i>so he'll probably be jailed.</i>

412
00:32:49,280 --> 00:32:50,120
POLICE STATION

413
00:33:04,560 --> 00:33:08,080
<i>He claimed he couldn't control himself,</i>

414
00:33:08,160 --> 00:33:11,440
<i>but the police likely won't accept that.</i>

415
00:33:18,080 --> 00:33:19,000
Kluay…

416
00:33:21,120 --> 00:33:22,520
What about Mr. Sarut?

417
00:33:22,600 --> 00:33:24,400
How is he?

418
00:33:25,160 --> 00:33:27,520
He's in the next room.

419
00:33:27,600 --> 00:33:31,080
The doctor said he's safe now.

420
00:33:32,880 --> 00:33:34,440
Are visitors allowed?

421
00:33:36,880 --> 00:33:38,200
I think so.

422
00:34:22,719 --> 00:34:23,719
My son.

423
00:34:29,880 --> 00:34:31,280
Please don't call me that.

424
00:34:48,719 --> 00:34:50,920
Yes, Mr. Warat.

425
00:34:54,360 --> 00:34:55,520
How are you?

426
00:34:56,800 --> 00:34:58,080
What did the doctor say?

427
00:34:59,120 --> 00:35:02,480
They said I'm out of danger now.

428
00:35:10,240 --> 00:35:11,680
Get well soon.

429
00:35:13,160 --> 00:35:14,040
Let's go, Kluay.

430
00:35:15,200 --> 00:35:16,080
Son…

431
00:35:18,400 --> 00:35:20,640
You really won't forgive me?

432
00:35:25,200 --> 00:35:26,800
A father…

433
00:35:32,560 --> 00:35:34,800
is someone who takes responsibility

434
00:35:35,320 --> 00:35:36,320
and raises a child.

435
00:35:37,880 --> 00:35:39,440
You've never done that.

436
00:35:40,320 --> 00:35:42,440
Do you really deserve
to call yourself a father?

437
00:35:44,320 --> 00:35:46,160
I was wrong. I'm sorry.

438
00:35:46,800 --> 00:35:47,840
I'm sorry.

439
00:35:53,400 --> 00:35:55,760
A father's duty is to raise

440
00:35:58,120 --> 00:35:59,800
and care for a child properly.

441
00:36:00,960 --> 00:36:02,160
Let me ask you.

442
00:36:04,240 --> 00:36:05,960
Have you ever done that?

443
00:36:12,600 --> 00:36:13,640
But I

444
00:36:14,480 --> 00:36:17,040
chose what was best for you.

445
00:36:17,120 --> 00:36:20,640
What you chose?! Was that the best?

446
00:36:23,080 --> 00:36:24,440
It led to

447
00:36:25,520 --> 00:36:29,000
Ms. Anong killing my father,
killing my mother,

448
00:36:29,080 --> 00:36:30,840
and nearly killing both of us.

449
00:36:30,920 --> 00:36:33,400
That's your idea of best?

450
00:36:33,480 --> 00:36:35,960
I regret that. I'm sorry.

451
00:36:37,560 --> 00:36:38,520
I'm sorry.

452
00:36:51,320 --> 00:36:52,400
It's my fault.

453
00:37:05,680 --> 00:37:06,840
NEXT EPISODE

454
00:37:06,920 --> 00:37:09,920
I thought I'd get another chance
to talk to my mom.

455
00:37:10,760 --> 00:37:13,240
Just because we can't see something
doesn't mean it doesn't exist.

456
00:37:16,320 --> 00:37:17,600
Will you marry me?

457
00:37:26,040 --> 00:37:27,040
What is this?

458
00:37:27,800 --> 00:37:28,960
Will you marry me?

459
00:37:29,920 --> 00:37:31,120
Arnon…

460
00:37:34,360 --> 00:37:37,840
Even though I'm not Kluay's real mother…

461
00:37:37,920 --> 00:37:40,760
Oh my, why did you say that?

462
00:37:41,280 --> 00:37:45,040
But I love her
as if she were my own daughter.

463
00:37:46,160 --> 00:37:48,560
Will I ever see Mom again?

464
00:37:49,680 --> 00:37:51,480
Your mother is always with you.

465
00:37:52,040 --> 00:37:54,840
In who you are, in every breath you take.

466
00:37:56,000 --> 00:37:58,480
There's nothing left
to worry about anymore.

467
00:38:01,920 --> 00:38:04,640
You have so many things to tell me.

468
00:38:06,880 --> 00:38:09,520
If only I hadn't been so greedy,

469
00:38:10,520 --> 00:38:11,440
things might have been better.

470
00:38:15,600 --> 00:38:16,840
<i>As for Kluay,</i>

471
00:38:18,080 --> 00:38:19,440
<i>please don't worry, Mom.</i>

472
00:38:21,040 --> 00:38:22,920
I promise I'll take care of her

473
00:38:23,880 --> 00:38:25,320
and love her with all my heart.

474
00:40:51,600 --> 00:40:53,920
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
